caseQuestions.answerText:
Although genetic testing is not available for all genes associated with Leigh syndrome, there is genetic testing available for both mitochondrial genes and nuclear genes associated with the condition. <br />
<br />
Please&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gtr/tests/?term=C0023264%5bDISCUI%5d&amp;display_string=Leigh%20syndrome&amp;condition=C0023264&amp;compare_labs=1" target="_blank">see a list of laboratories offering the genetic test&nbsp;</a>for Leigh syndrome by visiting&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gtr/" target="_blank">Genetic Testing Registry</a> (GTR), a centralized online resource for information about genetic tests. The intended audience for the GTR is health care providers and researchers. Patients and consumers with specific questions about a genetic test should contact a health care provider or a genetics professional.&nbsp;
